import numpy as np

1. Generacin de Datos Simulados

In[]:
np.random.seed(42)
n_sanos, n_cancer = 250, 250

# Biomarcadores sanos
cea_s = np.random.normal(2.5, 1, n_sanos)
ca19_s = np.random.normal(15, 8, n_sanos)
ca125_s = np.random.normal(20, 10, n_sanos)
afp_s = np.random.normal(5, 2, n_sanos)
g1_s, g2_s, g3_s = np.random.normal(5, 1.5, n_sanos), np.random.normal(4, 1.2, n_sanos), np.random.normal(6, 1.8, n_sanos)

# Biomarcadores cncer
cea_c = np.random.normal(25, 15, n_cancer)
ca19_c = np.random.normal(120, 80, n_cancer)
ca125_c = np.random.normal(85, 50, n_cancer)
afp_c = np.random.normal(30, 20, n_cancer)
g1_c, g2_c, g3_c = np.random.normal(15, 5, n_cancer), np.random.normal(2, 1, n_cancer), np.random.normal(12, 4, n_cancer)

# DataFrame
df = pd.DataFrame({
    'CEA': np.abs(np.concatenate([cea_s, cea_c])),
    'CA19_9': np.abs(np.concatenate([ca19_s, ca19_c])),
    'CA125': np.abs(np.concatenate([ca125_s, ca125_c])),
    'AFP': np.abs(np.concatenate([afp_s, afp_c])),
    'GeneExpr1': np.concatenate([g1_s, g1_c]),
    'GeneExpr2': np.concatenate([g2_s, g2_c]),
    'GeneExpr3': np.concatenate([g3_s, g3_c]),
    'Edad': np.concatenate([np.random.choice(['<40','40-60','>60'], n_sanos, p=[0.3,0.4,0.3]), np.random.choice(['<40','40-60','>60'], n_cancer, p=[0.1,0.3,0.6])]),
    'Sexo': np.random.choice(['M','F'], n_sanos+n_cancer, p=[0.48,0.52]),
    'Fumador': np.concatenate([np.random.choice(['No','Ex-fumador','Fumador'], n_sanos, p=[0.6,0.25,0.15]), np.random.choice(['No','Ex-fumador','Fumador'], n_cancer, p=[0.3,0.35,0.35])]),
    'Antecedentes_Familiares': np.concatenate([np.random.choice(['No','S'], n_sanos, p=[0.85,0.15]), np.random.choice(['No','S'], n_cancer, p=[0.6,0.4])]),
    'Estadio': np.concatenate([np.array(['Sano']*n_sanos), np.random.choice(['I','II','III','IV'], n_cancer, p=[0.2,0.3,0.3,0.2])]),
    'Diagnostico': ['Sano']*n_sanos + ['Adenocarcinoma']*n_cancer
})
print(f'Dataset: {df.shape}\n{df.Diagnostico.value_counts()}')

Dataset: (500, 13)
Diagnostico
Sano              250
Adenocarcinoma    250
Name: count, dtype: int64

In[]:
fig, axes = plt.subplots(3,3, figsize=(16,12))
fig.suptitle('Distribucin Biomarcadores: Sano vs Adenocarcinoma', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
for idx, bio in enumerate(biomarcadores):
    ax = axes[idx//3, idx%3]
    df[df.Diagnostico=='Sano'][bio].hist(ax=ax, alpha=0.6, bins=30, label='Sano', color='green', edgecolor='black')
    df[df.Diagnostico=='Adenocarcinoma'][bio].hist(ax=ax, alpha=0.6, bins=30, label='Adenocarcinoma', color='red', edgecolor='black')
    ax.set_xlabel(bio, fontsize=11)
    ax.set_ylabel('Frecuencia', fontsize=11)
    ax.legend()
    ax.grid(alpha=0.3)
for i in range(len(biomarcadores), 9):
    fig.delaxes(axes[i//3, i%3])
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

2.2 Box Plots

In[]:
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2,4, figsize=(18,10))
fig.suptitle('Box Plots de Biomarcadores', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
axes = axes.flatten()
for idx, bio in enumerate(biomarcadores):
    ax = axes[idx]
    data = [df[df.Diagnostico=='Sano'][bio], df[df.Diagnostico=='Adenocarcinoma'][bio]]
    bp = ax.boxplot(data, labels=['Sano','Adenocarcinoma'], patch_artist=True)
    for patch, color in zip(bp['boxes'], ['lightgreen','lightcoral']):
        patch.set_facecolor(color)
    ax.set_title(bio, fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
    ax.set_ylabel('Valor', fontsize=10)
    ax.grid(alpha=0.3)

plt.show()

2.5 Variables Clnicas

In[]:
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2,2, figsize=(14,10))
fig.suptitle('Variables Clnicas por Diagnstico', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
vars_cat = ['Edad','Sexo','Fumador','Antecedentes_Familiares']
for idx, var in enumerate(vars_cat):
    ax = axes[idx//2, idx%2]
    ct = pd.crosstab(df[var], df.Diagnostico, normalize='index')*100
    ct.plot(kind='bar', ax=ax, color=['green','red'], alpha=0.7)
    ax.set_title(var, fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
    ax.set_ylabel('Porcentaje (%)', fontsize=10)
    ax.legend(['Sano','Adenocarcinoma'])
    ax.grid(alpha=0.3, axis='y')
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45 if var=='Fumador' else 0, ha='right' if var=='Fumador' else 'center')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

3. Preparacin de Datos

In[]:
df_ml = df.drop('Estadio', axis=1)
y = (df_ml.Diagnostico=='Sano').astype(int).values
X_cont = df_ml[biomarcadores].values
X_cat = pd.get_dummies(df_ml[['Edad','Sexo','Fumador','Antecedentes_Familiares']], drop_first=False)
X = np.concatenate([X_cont, X_cat.values], axis=1)
feature_names = biomarcadores + list(X_cat.columns)
print(f'Features: {X.shape[1]}\nClases: Adenocarcinoma={np.sum(y==0)}, Sano={np.sum(y==1)}')

Features: 17
Clases: Adenocarcinoma=250, Sano=250
In[]:
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.25, random_state=42, stratify=y)
print(f'Train: {X_train.shape[0]}, Test: {X_test.shape[0]}')

Train: 375, Test: 125
In[]:
scaler = StandardScaler()
n_cont = len(biomarcadores)
X_train_sc, X_test_sc = X_train.copy(), X_test.copy()
X_train_sc[:,:n_cont] = scaler.fit_transform(X_train[:,:n_cont])
X_test_sc[:,:n_cont] = scaler.transform(X_test[:,:n_cont])
print('Normalizacin completada')

Normalizacin completada

4. Modelos ML

4.1 Regresin Logstica

In[]:
lr = LogisticRegression(random_state=42, max_iter=1000)
lr.fit(X_train_sc, y_train)
y_pred_lr = lr.predict(X_test_sc)
y_prob_lr = lr.predict_proba(X_test_sc)[:,1]
print('='*60)
print('REGRESIN LOGSTICA')
print('='*60)
print(f'Accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_lr):.4f}')
print(f'Precision: {precision_score(y_test, y_pred_lr):.4f}')
print(f'Recall: {recall_score(y_test, y_pred_lr):.4f}')
print(f'F1: {f1_score(y_test, y_pred_lr):.4f}')
print(f'AUC-ROC: {roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob_lr):.4f}')
print('\n', classification_report(y_test, y_pred_lr, target_names=['Adenocarcinoma','Sano']))

5. Comparacin de Modelos

5.1 Mtricas

In[]:
modelos = ['Logistic Regression','Random Forest','Gradient Boosting','SVM']
y_preds = [y_pred_lr, y_pred_rf, y_pred_gb, y_pred_svm]
y_probs = [y_prob_lr, y_prob_rf, y_prob_gb, y_prob_svm]

res = pd.DataFrame({
    'Modelo': modelos,
    'Accuracy': [accuracy_score(y_test,yp) for yp in y_preds],
    'Precision': [precision_score(y_test,yp) for yp in y_preds],
    'Recall': [recall_score(y_test,yp) for yp in y_preds],
    'F1': [f1_score(y_test,yp) for yp in y_preds],
    'AUC-ROC': [roc_auc_score(y_test,ypr) for ypr in y_probs]
})
print(res)

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12,6))
x = np.arange(len(modelos))
width = 0.15
metrics = ['Accuracy','Precision','Recall','F1','AUC-ROC']
colors = ['#FF6B6B','#4ECDC4','#45B7D1','#FFA07A','#98D8C8']
for i, m in enumerate(metrics):
    ax.bar(x+i*width, res[m], width, label=m, color=colors[i], alpha=0.8)
ax.set_xlabel('Modelos', fontweight='bold')
ax.set_ylabel('Score', fontweight='bold')
ax.set_title('Comparacin de Mtricas', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold', pad=20)
ax.set_xticks(x+width*2)
ax.set_xticklabels(modelos, rotation=15, ha='right')
ax.legend()
ax.grid(alpha=0.3, axis='y')
ax.set_ylim([0,1.05])
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

7. Conclusiones

Resumen de Resultados:

  1. Dataset: 500 pacientes (250 sanos, 250 con adenocarcinoma)
  2. Biomarcadores: CEA, CA19-9, CA125, AFP, expresin gnica
  3. Variables clnicas: Edad, sexo, fumador, antecedentes familiares

Hallazgos Clave:

  • Los biomarcadores CEA, CA19-9 y CA125 muestran diferencias significativas entre grupos
  • Las variables clnicas aportan informacin complementaria
  • Los modelos de ensemble (Random Forest, Gradient Boosting) logran mejor desempeo
  • AUC-ROC > 0.90 en los mejores modelos, indicando excelente capacidad de discriminacin

Recomendaciones:

  1. Validar modelos con datos reales de pacientes
  2. Considerar validacin cruzada y anlisis de sensibilidad
  3. Evaluar umbrales de decisin ptimos segn contexto clnico
  4. Implementar seguimiento prospectivo para validacin externa
